results.name: Expansion of (q*j(q))^(11/24) where j(q) is the elliptic modular invariant (A000521).
comment: In general, the expansion of (q*j(q))^m, where j(q) is the elliptic modular invariant (A000521) and m <> 0, is asymptotic to exp(4*Pi*sqrt(m*n)) * m^(1/4) / (sqrt(2) * n^(3/4)) if 3*m is the positive integer, else is asymptotic to (-1)^n * 3^(3*m) * Gamma(1/3)^(18*m) * exp(Pi*sqrt(3)*(n-m)) / (2^(3*m) * Pi^(12*m) * Gamma(-3*m) * n^(3*m + 1)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 06 2018
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..426
mathematica: CoefficientList[Series[(65536 + x*QPochhammer[-1, x]^24)^(11/8) / (2*QPochhammer[-1, x])^11, {x, 0, 20}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Sep 23 2017 *)
